    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1982-01-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1982-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <head>139. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_CWP_1">Clark</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d139fn1">Source: Reagan Library, Guhin,
                        Michael A.: Files, 01/20/1982–01/22/1982. Secret. A stamped notation on the
                        document reads: “The President has seen.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1982-01-26">January 26, 1982</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Decision Directive and Public Statement on US Law of the Sea Policy</item>
                </list>
                <p>As directed at the January 21 <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> meeting on
                    this subject,<note n="2" xml:id="d139fn2">See <ref target="#d138">Document
                            138</ref>.</note> we have prepared a decision directive (Tab A)<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d139fn3">Tab A, not attached, is printed in <ref
                            target="#d140">Document 140</ref>.</note> and public statement (Tab
                        B).<note n="4" xml:id="d139fn4">Not attached. See <hi rend="italic">Public
                            Papers:</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName>
                        </hi>, 1982, Book I, p. 92.</note> These reflect your decisions and the
                    agreement in that meeting. State concurs. Aram Bakshian concurs in the
                    statement.</p>
                <p>We should issue the directive and release the statement as early in the week of
                    January 25 as possible. We will background the statement with <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJL_1">Jim Malone</persName>, your Special Representative for
                    Law of the Sea. Key capitals have been advised to expect a favorable
                    announcement shortly.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">RECOMMENDATION</p>
                <p>That you approve and sign the National Security Decision Directive (Tab A) and
                    approve release of the Presidential statement (Tab B).<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d139fn5">The President checked and initialed the approve
                        option.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
